location: Divisadero Street and Golden Gate Avenue
Description: On November 12, 2021 at 1:23 PM PST a Waymo Autonomous Vehicle (“Waymo AV”) operating in San Francisco, CA was in a collision involving a passenger vehicle at Divisadero Street at Turk Street. The Waymo AV was stopped at a red light on Divisadero Street at Turk Street. When the traffic light turned green, the passenger vehicle behind the Waymo AV made contact with the rear of the Waymo AV. At the time of the impact, the Waymo AV’s Level 4 ADS was engaged in autonomous mode, and a test driver was present (in the driver’s seating position). The Waymo AV sustained minor damage, and the trailing passenger vehicle sustained minor damage.

On November 15, 2021 at 2:20 AM PST a Waymo Autonomous Vehicle (“Waymo AV”) operating in San Francisco, CA was in a collision involving a passenger vehicle at Noriega Street at 40th Avenue. The Waymo AV was stopped at a stop sign at Noriega Street at 40th Avenue when a passenger vehicle made contact with the rear of the Waymo AV. At the time of the impact, the Waymo AV’s Level 4 ADS was engaged in autonomous mode, and a test driver was present (in the driver’s seating position). The Waymo AV’s rear bumper and undercarriage sustained moderate damage, and the passenger vehicle’s front bumper and hood sustained moderate damage.

location: Scotia Ave, Thornton Ave, and Bridgeview Dr
Description: On November 26, 2021 at 8:02 PM PST a Waymo Autonomous Vehicle (“Waymo AV”) operating in San Francisco, CA was in a collision involving a passenger vehicle at Scotia Avenue, Thornton Avenue, and Bridgeview Drive. The Waymo AV was traveling southbound on Scotia Avenue, a narrow road with vehicles parked on both sides, and approaching the intersection with Thornton Avenue and Bridgeview Drive. A passenger vehicle approaching from the right of the Waymo AV on eastbound Thornton Avenue made a left turn in front of the Waymo AV to head northbound on Scotia Avenue. The Waymo AV slowed to a near stop and nudged to its right in order to share the narrow road with the oncoming vehicle and then came to a stop at the stop sign as the oncoming vehicle completed its turn. At approximately 5 mph, the turning passenger vehicle made contact with Waymo AV’s sensor hardware housing on the driver side rear corner fender of the stopped Waymo AV. At the time of the impact, the Waymo AV’s Level 4 ADS was engaged in autonomous mode, and a test driver was present (in the driver’s seating position). The Waymo AV sustained minor damage to the sensor hardware housing (which was the reason for towing the Waymo AV) and the passenger vehicle left the scene without exchanging information.

On November 28, 2021 at 6:08 PM PST a Waymo Autonomous Vehicle (“Waymo AV”) operating in San Francisco, CA was in a collision involving a passenger vehicle at Clay Street at Franklin Street. The Waymo AV was stopped at a red light on eastbound Clay Street at Franklin Street when a passenger vehicle struck the Waymo AV’s rear bumper. At the time of the impact, the Waymo AV’s Level 4 ADS was engaged in autonomous mode, and a test driver was present (in the driver’s seating position). The Waymo AV’s rear bumper sustained damage, and the passenger vehicle’s front bumper sustained damage.

location: 16th Street at Market and Noe Street
Description: On December 3, 2021 at 12:23 PM PST a Waymo Autonomous Vehicle (“Waymo AV”) operating in San Francisco, CA was in a collision involving a passenger vehicle at 16th Street at Market and Noe Street.As the Waymo AV approached the intersection of 16th Street and Market Street, it stopped behind traffic at a red light. After the Waymo AV was fully stopped, a passenger vehicle reversed out of a parking spot perpendicular to the Waymo AV and made contact with the passenger side rear corner of the Waymo AV. At the time of the impact, the Waymo AV’s Level 4 ADS was engaged in autonomous mode, and a test driver was present in the driver’s seating position. Both vehicles sustained minor damage to their rear bumpers.

On December 7, 2021 at 10:47 AM PST a Waymo Autonomous Vehicle (“Waymo AV”) operating in San Francisco, CA was in a collision involving an SUV at Oak Street at Stanyan Street. While in autonomous mode, the Waymo AV came to a stop at a stop sign on Oak Street. While the ADV was stopped, waiting for a pedestrian to cross and for traffic on Stanyan Street to clear, an SUV approached the Waymo AV from behind and made contact with the rear of the Waymo AV. At the time of the impact, the Waymo AV’s Level 4 ADS was engaged in autonomous mode, and a test driver was present (in the driver’s seating position). The Waymo AV sustained minor damage to the rear bumper.

On December 12, 2022 at 4:54 PM PST a Waymo Autonomous Vehicle (“Waymo AV”) operating in San Francisco, California was in a collision involving an SUV on Monterey Boulevard at Circular Avenue.The Waymo AV was stopped facing east on Monterey Boulevard behind stopped traffic in the left-most through lane in autonomous mode. An SUV approached from behind and attempted to change lanes into the left turn lane, making contact with the left rear sensor of the Waymo AV. At the time of the impact, the Waymo AV’s Level 4 ADS was engaged in autonomous mode, and a test driver was present (in the driver’s seating position). Both vehicles sustained damage.

On December 13, 2022 at 12:35 PM PST a Waymo Autonomous Vehicle (“Waymo AV”) operating in San Francisco, California was in a collision involving a passenger vehicle on 19th Avenue at Ulloa Street.The Waymo AV was stopped facing south on 19th Avenue for a red light in the right lane of the three-lane street while in autonomous mode. A passenger vehicle approached from behind and made contact with the rear of the Waymo AV. At the time of the impact, the Waymo AV’s Level 4 ADS was engaged in autonomous mode, and a test driver was present (in the driver’s seating position). The Waymo sustained damage.

On December 29, 2022 at 3:15 AM PST a Waymo Autonomous Vehicle (“Waymo AV”) operating in San Francisco, California was in a collision involving a passenger vehicle on 3rd Street and Mariposa Street.The Waymo AV was stopped facing north on 3rd Street for a red light in the right lane of the three-lane street while in autonomous mode. A passenger vehicle approached from behind and stopped behind the Waymo AV before eventually proceeding forward and making contact with the rear of the Waymo AV while the AV was still stopped at the red light. At the time of the impact, the Waymo AV’s Level 4 ADS was engaged in autonomous mode, and a test driver was present (in the driver’s seating position). The Waymo sustained damage.

location: Manhattan Place at West Adams Boulevard
Description: On January 8, 2023 at 12:05 PM PT a Waymo Autonomous Vehicle (“Waymo AV”) operating in Los Angeles, California was in a collision involving an SUV on Manhattan Place at West Adams Boulevard.  The Waymo AV was traveling northbound on Manhattan Place when it came to a stop to yield to an oncoming vehicle in a narrow roadway with parked vehicles on both sides of the street. As the oncoming SUV passed the Waymo AV, the driver’s side rear of the SUV made contact with the driver’s side rear of the Waymo AV. At the time of the impact, the Waymo AV’s Level 4 ADS was engaged in autonomous mode. The Waymo AV sustained damage and the SUV left the scene.

location: Watt Way and West Exposition Boulevard
Description: On February 5, 2024 at 10:01 PM PT a Waymo Autonomous Vehicle (“Waymo AV”) operating in Los Angeles, California was in a collision involving a gate at Watt Way and West Exposition Boulevard.The Waymo AV was traveling south on Watt when it approached an automatic gate as it had started to close. The right side of the Waymo AV made contact with the door of the gate. At the time of the impact, the Waymo AV’s Level 4 ADS was engaged in autonomous mode. The Waymo AV sustained damage.

On February 18, 2024 at 1:03 AM PT a Waymo Autonomous Vehicle ("Waymo AV") operating in San Francisco, California was in a collision involving a passenger car on The Embarcadero at Washington Street.The Waymo AV was stopped in traffic for a red light on The Embarcadero southbound when a passenger car approached from behind and made contact with the rear of the Waymo AV. At the time of the impact, the Waymo AV's Level 4 ADS was engaged in autonomous mode, and a test driver was present (in the driver's seating position). Both vehicles sustained damage and the passenger car left the scene.

location: S Figueroa Street at Venice Boulevard
Description: On March 8, 2024 at 12:06 PM PT a Waymo Autonomous Vehicle ("Waymo AV") operating in Los Angeles, California was in a collision involving a passenger car near the 1600 block of S. Figueroa Street. The Waymo AV made a left turn from W. 17th Street onto S. Figueroa Street and came to a stop in a queue of stopped traffic. A passenger car traveling straight on S. Figueroa Street behind the Waymo AV made contact with the rear of the Waymo AV.  At the time of the impact, the Waymo AV's Level 4 ADS was engaged in autonomous mode. The Waymo AV sustained damage and the passenger car left the scene.

On March 14, 2024 at 2:42 PM PT a Waymo Autonomous Vehicle (“Waymo AV”) operating in Los Angeles, California was in a collision involving a passenger car on S Figueroa Street at 7th Street. The Waymo AV was traveling northeast on S Figueroa Street in the lane adjacent to the rightmost, bus-only lane. As the Waymo AV approached the intersection with 7th Street, it came to a stop behind another vehicle stopped in traffic. As a passenger car was passing the Waymo AV in the bus lane to the right of the Waymo AV, the passenger car made contact with the passenger side of the Waymo AV. At the time of the impact, the Waymo AV’s Level 4 ADS was engaged in autonomous mode. The Waymo AV sustained damage and the passenger car left the scene.Waymo is reporting this crash under Request No. 2 of Standing General Order 2021-01.

location: Jack London Alley at Varney Place
Description: On April 3, 2023 at 10:56 PM PST a Waymo Autonomous Vehicle (“Waymo AV”) operating in San Francisco, California was in a collision involving an SUV on Jack London Alley at Varney Place.While traveling northwest on Jack London Alley, the Waymo AV came to a stop to yield to an oncoming SUV in a narrow passageway. The SUV proceeded around the Waymo AV and made contact with the left rear sensor housing of the Waymo AV. At the time of the impact, the Waymo AV’s Level 4 ADS was engaged in autonomous mode, and a test driver was present (in the driver’s seating position). The driver of the SUV stopped briefly but left before sharing their information. The Waymo sustained damage.

On April 6, 2023 at 10:48 AM PST a Waymo Autonomous Vehicle (“Waymo AV”) operating in San Francisco, California was in a collision involving a heavy truck on Randall Street near Harper Street. The Waymo AV was proceeding northwest on Randall Street near the intersection with Harper Street when it came to a stop to yield to a heavy truck traveling southeast on Randall Street. As the heavy truck drove past the Waymo AV, the driver’s side section of the heavy truck made contact with the rear driver’s side sensor of the Waymo AV. The heavy truck then left the scene. At the time of the impact, the Waymo AV’s Level 4 ADS was engaged in autonomous mode. The Waymo AV sustained damage.

The Waymo AV was traveling east on 25th Street between Sanchez Street and Vicksburg Street when it approached an SUV that was stopped in the lane in front of the Waymo AV. The Waymo AV began passing the stopped SUV on the left when the SUV began reversing in the lane. The Waymo AV then stopped behind and to the left of the SUV, and the SUV continued reversing and began a turning maneuver to enter a parking space. The left side of the SUV made contact with the front right corner of the Waymo AV. At the time of the impact, the Waymo AV was stopped and the AV’s Level 4 ADS was engaged in autonomous mode. Both vehicles sustained damage.

On May 6, 2023 at 8:48 PM PT a Waymo Autonomous Vehicle (“Waymo AV”) operating in San Francisco, California was in a collision involving a passenger vehicle on Post Street at Webster Street.While traveling west on Post Street, the Waymo AV was executing a pullover maneuver in autonomous mode and made contact with the left rear bumper of a parked vehicle. At the time of the impact, the Waymo AV’s Level 4 ADS was engaged in autonomous mode. Both vehicles sustained damage.

On May 7, 2023 at 3:27 PM PDT a Waymo Autonomous Vehicle (“Waymo AV”) operating in San Francisco, California was in a collision involving a cyclist on Bay Street near Mason Street. The Waymo AV was traveling westbound in the left lane on Bay Street and had just passed Mason Street when it detected an oncoming pickup truck traveling eastbound in the Waymo AV’s lane. The Waymo AV stopped and the pickup truck re-entered the correct lane for eastbound traffic and passed the Waymo AV. The pickup truck was immediately followed by a large group of cyclists traveling eastbound in multiple lanes of the roadway, including the right lanes and on the wrong side of the double-yellow centerline. The Waymo AV remained stopped as the oncoming cyclists rode around both sides of the Waymo AV. One cyclist then made contact with the front of the stationary Waymo AV, and then immediately left the scene. At the time of the impact, the Waymo AV’s Level 4 ADS was engaged in autonomous mode. The Waymo AV sustained damage.

On May 21, 2023 at 10:56 AM PT a Waymo Autonomous Vehicle (“Waymo AV”) operating in San Francisco, California was in a collision involving a small dog on Toland Street at Toland Place.The Waymo AV was traveling southwest on Toland Street when a small dog ran into the street in front of the Waymo AV. The Waymo AV then made contact with the dog, which did not survive. At the time of the impact, the Waymo AV’s Level 4 ADS was engaged in autonomous mode, and a test driver was present (in the driver’s seating position). The Waymo AV sustained damage.

On June 5, 2023 at 12:53 PM PT a Waymo Autonomous Vehicle (“Waymo AV”) operating in San Francisco, California was in a collision involving a van in a parking lot at 3911 3rd Street.The Waymo AV came to a stop while yielding to a pickup truck which was reversing into a perpendicular parking space in front of the Waymo AV. While the Waymo AV was stopped, a van which was in a parking space immediately to the right of the Waymo AV began reversing out of the parking space. The rear of the van made contact with the right side of the Waymo AV. The Waymo AV sustained damage. At the time of the impact, the Waymo AV’s Level 4 ADS was engaged in autonomous mode.

On June 11, 2023 at 3:44 PM PT a Waymo Autonomous Vehicle (“Waymo AV”) operating in San Francisco, California was in a collision involving a passenger car on Santiago Street near 42nd Avenue.The Waymo AV was parallel parked along the curb on eastbound Santiago Street when a passenger car pulled up behind the Waymo AV. The front of the passenger car made contact with the rear of the Waymo AV. At the time of the impact, the Waymo AV’s Level 4 ADS was engaged in autonomous mode. The Waymo AV sustained damage.

On June 28, 2023 at 9:19 PM PT a Waymo Autonomous Vehicle (“Waymo AV”) operating in San Francisco, California was in a collision involving a pickup truck on Great Highway near Kirkham Street. The Waymo AV was parallel parked along the curb on southbound Great Highway when a pickup truck that was initially parked directly behind the Waymo AV began to maneuver out of its parking spot. As the pickup truck pulled out of the parking spot, it initiated a multi-turn maneuver and reversed into the parked Waymo AV. The rear passenger's side corner of the pickup truck made contact with the driver side rear of the Waymo AV. At the time of the impact, the Waymo AV’s Level 4 ADS was engaged in autonomous mode. The Waymo AV sustained damage.

On June 29, 2023 at 7:50 AM PT a Waymo Autonomous Vehicle (“Waymo AV”) operating in San Francisco, CA was in a collision involving a pickup truck on Jersey Street at Church Street. The Waymo AV was traveling eastbound on Jersey Street and stopped at a stop sign at the intersection of Church Street. While yielding to pedestrians crossing the street, a pickup truck traveling directly behind the Waymo AV made contact with the rear of the Waymo AV. At the time of the impact, the Waymo AV’s Level 4 ADS was engaged in autonomous mode. The Waymo AV sustained damage.

On June 29, 2023 at 11:18 PM PT a Waymo Autonomous Vehicle (“Waymo AV”) operating in Los Angeles, California was in a collision involving a pick-up truck on 4th Street at S. June Street.The Waymo AV was traveling eastbound on 4th Street and stopped at a stop sign at the intersection of S. June Street when a pick-up truck approached the Waymo AV from behind and made contact with the rear of the Waymo AV. The Waymo AV test driver took manual control of the Waymo AV to pull over, and the pick-up truck made further contact the Waymo AV. At the time of the initial impact, the Waymo AV’s Level 4 ADS was engaged in autonomous mode, and a test driver was present (in the driver’s seating position). The Waymo AV sustained damage.

On July 8, 2023 at 3:08 PM PT a Waymo Autonomous Vehicle (“Waymo AV”) operating in Los Angeles, California was in a collision involving a cyclist on S. Alameda Street at 6th Street.The Waymo AV was traveling southbound on S. Alameda Street and preparing to make a right turn onto westbound 6th Street. As the Waymo AV was yielding to cross-traffic and preparing to make a right turn, a cyclist was traveling eastbound on 6th Street and heading the wrong way in the bike lane. The cyclist then turned left, northbound, onto S. Alameda Street, continuing to travel the wrong direction in the bike lane. As the Waymo AV slowly proceeded forward, the cyclist passed the Waymo AV and made contact with the rear passenger side sensor of the Waymo AV. At the time of the impact, the Waymo AV’s Level 4 ADS was engaged in autonomous mode, and a test driver was present (in the driver’s seating position). The Waymo AV sustained damage and the cyclist did not stop, leaving the scene without exchanging information.

location: Leavenworth Street at Golden Gate Avenue
Description: On July 21, 2023 at 9:51 AM PT a Waymo Autonomous Vehicle (“Waymo AV”) operating in San Francisco, California was in a collision involving a passenger car on Leavenworth Street at Golden Gate Avenue.  The collision occurred while the Waymo AV was stopped in the leftmost lane of a two-lane, one-way road at the intersection of Leavenworth Street at Golden Gate Avenue. The Waymo AV was stopped before the intersection, yielding to blocking cross-traffic when the light turned yellow. At that point, a passenger car that had been stopped behind the Waymo AV passed the Waymo AV on the left and proceeded into the intersection. While passing the Waymo AV, the passenger car’s rear passenger side door made contact with the driver side rear of the Waymo AV. At the time of the impact, the Waymo AV’s Level 4 ADS was engaged in autonomous mode. The passenger car did not stop but appears to have sustained damage.

On July 22, 2023 at 11:11 AM PT a Waymo Autonomous Vehicle (“Waymo AV”) operating in San Francisco, California was in a collision involving a passenger vehicle on 13th Street east of Folsom Street.The Waymo AV was facing east while stopped just left of the right turn lane on 13th Street, with stopped traffic to the right. After waiting to merge, the Waymo AV reversed slightly to reroute and while doing so, a sensor on the right front of the Waymo AV made contact with the left rear side of a vehicle in the right turn lane. At the time of the impact, the Waymo AV’s Level 4 ADS was engaged in autonomous mode. The other vehicle sustained damage.

On July 25, 2023 at 3:04 PM PT a Waymo Autonomous Vehicle (“Waymo AV”) operating in San Francisco, California was in a collision involving a pickup truck on Harrison Street at 2nd Street. The Waymo AV was parallel parked along the curb on eastbound Harrison Street at 2nd Street when it began to pull away from the curb and into traffic. As the Waymo AV pulled away from the curb, a pickup truck that was traveling behind the Waymo AV then made contact with the rear of the Waymo AV. At the time of the impact, the Waymo AV’s Level 4 ADS was engaged in autonomous mode, and a test driver was present (in the driver’s seating position). Both vehicles sustained damage.

On July 29, 2023 at 2:57 PM PT a Waymo Autonomous Vehicle (“Waymo AV”) operating in Santa Monica, California was in a collision involving a cyclist on Colorado Avenue near Ocean Avenue.The Waymo AV was stopped in traffic on southwestbound Colorado Avenue when a cyclist that had been traveling behind the Waymo AV passed the Waymo AV on the right. As the cyclist passed the Waymo AV, the cyclist made contact with the front passenger side sensor of the Waymo AV. At the time of the impact, the Waymo AV’s Level 4 ADS was engaged in autonomous mode, and a test driver was present (in the driver’s seating position). The Waymo AV sustained damage and the cyclist did not stop, leaving the scene without exchanging information.

On August 2, 2023 at 10:09 PM PT a Waymo Autonomous Vehicle (“Waymo AV”) operating in San Francisco, California was in a collision involving an SUV on Bush Street at Polk Street.The Waymo AV was stopped at a red light on eastbound Bush Street at Polk Street. Shortly after the traffic light turned green and the Waymo AV began to proceed forward, the Waymo AV slowed to a stop. The SUV that was traveling closely behind the Waymo AV made contact with the rear of the Waymo AV. At the time of the impact, the Waymo AV’s Level 4 ADS was engaged in autonomous mode. Both vehicles sustained damage, and the trailing SUV left the scene without exchanging information. A passenger in the Waymo AV reported injuries.

On August 19, 2023 at 4:45 PM PT a Waymo Autonomous Vehicle (“Waymo AV”) operating in San Francisco, California was in a collision involving a passenger car on 13th Street at Mission Street.The Waymo AV entered the slip lane which connects westbound 13th Street to northbound Mission Street and came to a stop to yield to cross-traffic on Mission Street. As the Waymo AV was stopped, the front of the passenger car which was traveling behind the Waymo AV made contact with the rear of the Waymo AV. At the time of the impact, the Waymo AV’s Level 4 ADS was engaged in autonomous mode, and a test driver was present (in the driver’s seating position). The Waymo AV sustained damage.

location: Martin Luther King Jr. Drive at Crossover Drive
Description: On August 20, 2023 at 5:49 PM PT the mirror of a Waymo Autonomous Vehicle (“Waymo AV”) operating in San Francisco, CA was struck by a cyclist on Martin Luther King Jr. Drive at Crossover Drive.The Waymo AV was stopped in traffic on eastbound Martin Luther King Jr. Drive at the intersection with Crossover Drive, when a cyclist that had been traveling behind the Waymo AV passed the Waymo AV on the left. As the cyclist passed the Waymo AV, the cyclist made contact with the driver side mirror of the Waymo AV. At the time of the impact, the Waymo AV’s Level 4 ADS was engaged in autonomous mode, and a test driver was present (in the driver’s seating position). The Waymo AV sustained damage and the cyclist did not stop, leaving the scene without exchanging information.

On August 23, 2023 at 9:54 PM PT a Waymo Autonomous Vehicle (“Waymo AV”) operating in San Francisco, California was in a collision involving a heavy truck on Mason Street at Vandewater Street.The Waymo AV was traveling northbound on Mason Street when it approached a heavy truck and trailer that was stopped in the adjacent lane on the left side of the street. As the Waymo began to slowly pass the truck, the truck initiated a reversing turn maneuver into a loading bay on the left side of Mason Street. The Waymo AV then came to a stop, and as the Waymo AV was initiating its own reversing maneuver to clear the path for the truck, the right side of the trailer made contact with the front driver’s side corner of the Waymo AV. At the time of the impact, the Waymo AV’s Level 4 ADS was engaged in autonomous mode. The Waymo AV sustained damage.

On August 24, 2023 at 4:39 PM PT a Waymo Autonomous Vehicle (“Waymo AV”) operating in Santa Monica, California was in a collision involving a passenger car on Michigan Avenue at Euclid Street. The Waymo AV was traversing a roundabout at the intersection of Michigan Avenue at Euclid Street when it slowed to a stop for other vehicles approaching and in the roundabout. The front of the passenger car that was in the roundabout behind the Waymo AV made contact with the rear of the Waymo AV. Both vehicles sustained damage.

On September 20th, 2023 at 9:00 PM PT a Waymo Autonomous Vehicle (“Waymo AV”) operating in San Francisco, California was in a collision involving a passenger car on US-101 exit ramp 429B at the intersection with Bayshore Boulevard.The Waymo AV was proceeding south on exit ramp 429B in the leftmost lane and entered the slip lane to proceed north on Bayshore Boulevard. As the Waymo AV came to a stop for a red light at the intersection with Bayshore Boulevard, the front of the passenger car which was following behind the Waymo AV made contact with the rear of the Waymo AV. The Waymo AV sustained damage. At the time of the impact, the Waymo AV’s Level 4 ADS was engaged in autonomous mode, and a test driver was present.

On November 3, 2023 at 3:44 PM PT a Waymo Autonomous Vehicle ("Waymo AV") operating in San Francisco, California was in a collision involving a passenger car on 3rd Street at Stevenson Street.The Waymo AV was stopped in the rightmost non-HOV lane on northbound 3rd Street waiting for the intersection at Stevenson Street to clear during a green light. The passenger car behind the Waymo AV was rear-ended by a pickup truck, causing the front of the passenger car to make contact with the rear of the Waymo AV. At the time of the impact, the Waymo AV’s Level 4 ADS was engaged in autonomous mode, and a test driver was present (in the driver’s seating position). All three vehicles sustained damage.

location: West 7th Street at South Park View Street
Description: On November 22, 2023 at 7:59 PM PT a Waymo Autonomous Vehicle (“Waymo AV”) operating in Los Angeles, California was in a collision involving a passenger vehicle on West 7th Street at South Park View Street.The Waymo AV was stopped for a red light facing southeast on West 7th Street at South Park View Street when a passenger vehicle approached from behind and made contact with the rear of the Waymo AV. At the time of the impact, the Waymo AV’s Level 4 ADS was engaged in autonomous mode, and a test driver was present (in the driver’s seating position). The Waymo AV sustained damage.

At about 11:35 am our vehicle (car 1) was waiting behind a USPS truck to make an unprotected left turn, meanwhile one other vehicle (car 2) waited behind our vehicle.   Another non involved vehicle notices the queue of vehicles and passes on the right in the bike lane.  As the USPS truck begins to make the turn, car 1 begins to move forward at 7 MPH then slowed to 3 MPH when yielding to the vehicle passing in the bike lane. Car 2 directly behind us strikes our passenger rear bumper.  The safety driver then disengaged the vehicle (car 1) and moved into a nearby parking lot to exchange information.

At 3:27 PM on 11/03/2021, a driver from Weride was operating one of our autonomous vehicles in autonomous mode on the on-ramp to CA 87 S from Charcot Avenue in North San Jose.  Our car was in the queue of traffic waiting for the metering light.   While our car was stationary (0 MPH), the other car involved accelerated slightly to about 5 MPH, which resulted in a minor rear end collision.  Our driver and the other party pulled over onto the shoulder.  There were no injuries and information was exchanged.  Since damage to our car was minimal, it was driven back to the office in manual mode.

location: On 2nd St Left turn to  E San Fernando St
Description: At approximately 12:56pm, a WeRide vehicle (car 1) was slowing to a stop (< 3mph) on 2nd street at the intersection of East San Fernando st. to turn left in an effort to yield to crossing pedestrians. At this time a Toyota Prius (car 2) traveling (>10mph) had slammed into car 1's rear - causing damage primarily to car 1. Both parties pulled over to a safe location to exchange information but the driver of car 2 could not provide a valid insurance or registration certificate.

On Monday May 1st at 11:41am a Weride autonomous vehicle (Vehicle 1) was in Autonomous Mode stopped at the intersection of Bay St towards Columbus Ave appropriately yielding to a illegally U turning skateboard on Bay St North to South direction in front of the AV (Vehicle 1). While yielding, a bicyclist was coming from behind our AV (Vehicle 1) head was turned left possibly looking for cross traffic. When the cyclist turned his head forward, it was too late to react in time to our stopped vehicle(Vehicle 1) with the given distance and speed they were traveling at in which the cyclist collided with our vehicle (Vehicle 1). Our Weride safety officer immediately disengaged and hand signaled to the bicyclist to pull over to the closest safe place to park as to not obstruct traffic. As our safety officer parked and got out of the car to check on the bicyclist, the bicyclist was already on in motion on his bicycle and "fist bumped" our safety officer while passing by him and leaving the scene without exchanging any information.

location: E Trimble Rd between Junction Ave and Zanker Rd
Description: At 2:06pm a WeRide driverless vehicle (car 1) was stopped behind a big rig truck (vehicle 2). As our vehicle (car 1) was stopped behind the big rig truck, the big rig truck proceeded to reverse backwards and eventually collided into the WeRide vehicle (car 1). Both parties pulled over both involved vehicles and cooperated to exchange information. The damage sustained to the WeRide vehicle was moderate and the big rig truck did not have any damage.

location: On Embarcadero St left turning lane to Howard St
Description: At 1:54pm, a WeRide vehicle (Car 1) was stopped on Embarcadero St left turning lane to Howard St. As our vehicle (Car 1) was stopped for red traffic light, the toyota suv (Car 2) approaching from behind collided with our vehicle (Car 1). Both parties pulled over both involved vehicles and cooperated to exchange information. The damage sustained to the WeRide vehicle (Car 1) and toyota suv (Car 2) are minor.

A Zoox vehicle traveling in autonomous mode on Broadway St. towards Powell St. encountered a double-parked flatbed truck. The Zoox vehicle began to maneuver around the stationary truck and made slight contact with the left rear of the truck, causing a scrape on the passenger-side door of the Zoox vehicle; there was no damage to the truck. There were no injuries and police were not called.

A Zoox vehicle in autonomous mode was making a right turn to travel southwest onto 2nd Street from Folsom Street from lane 1 when Vehicle 2 crossed from lane 3 into the Zoox vehicle's lane and made contact with the Zoox vehicle's front sensors before making the right turn.  Vehicle 2 did not stop before leaving the scene. No information was exchanged. There were no injuries and the police were not called.

location: Embarcadero between Howard St. and Folsom St.
Description: A Zoox vehicle in autonomy was stopped with brake lights illuminated in traffic southbound on Embarcadero Street towards Folsom Street. When traffic ahead began to move the Zoox vehicle was appropriately following the car ahead at low speed when it was rear ended by Vehicle #2 at low speed. The other party did not stop to exchange information and left the scene. There were no injuries and police were not called.

A Zoox vehicle in autonomous mode was slowing to a stop with brake lights illuminated behind traffic on northbound 5th Street near Jesse Street when a vehicle behind made contact at approximately 10mph. There were no injuries and police were not called.

A Zoox vehicle was in autonomous mode while making a right lane change on Montgomery St facing north towards Clay St. A car entered traffic from a stop sign intersection on right without stopping and struck the Zoox vehicle's rear passenger side door, causing moderate damage. There were no injuries and police were not called.

A Zoox vehicle was stationary in autonomous mode on Montgomery St facing north towards Broadway St, yielding for an oncoming bus encroaching upon its lane. The bus struck the driver's side mirror, causing it to fold with minor damage. The bus driver did not stop, so no information was exchanged. There were no injuries and police were not called.

location: Mason St. and Ellis St. Intersection
Description: A Zoox vehicle in autonomous mode was proceeding straight through the intersection of Mason St. and Ellis St. when it was rear-ended by a passenger vehicle that was switching lanes and made contact with the Zoox vehicle's sensors. The other party left the scene. The police were not called, and there were no injuries.

A Zoox vehicle in autonomy was proceeding straight on Harrison St. in San Francisco, Ca, when a passenger vehicle turning left from 14th St. on to Harrison St. struck the rear of the Zoox vehicle damaging the sensors. There were no injuries and the police were not called.

A Zoox vehicle in autonomous mode was traveling on Folsom Street straight through the 5th Street intersection when a passenger vehicle in the right adjacent lane attempted to make a left turn in front of the Zoox vehicle onto 5th Street. The rear left bumper of the turning passenger vehicle made contact with the front right side of the Zoox vehicle. There were no injuries, and the police were not called.

A Zoox vehicle in autonomous mode was stopped in traffic at the intersection of Harrison St. and 13 St. when a passenger vehicle from behind hit the Zoox vehicle’s rear bumper and sensors at a low speed. There were no injuries and police were not called.

The stationary Zoox vehicle was in autonomous mode heading northbound on Union St. Contact occurred when the Zoox vehicle was stopped at a stop sign at the intersection of Union St. and Grant St., when it was rear-ended by an electric scooter. The scooter was following closely behind the Zoox vehicle and the scooter driver was not focused on the Zoox vehicle in front of it, when the scooter's front tire made contact with the rear bumper of the Zoox vehicle.  There were no injuries.

The stationary Zoox vehicle was in autonomous mode at the stop sign on Polk St. heading northbound towards Green St. The Zoox vehicle moved forward slightly, then slowed down in caution to a pedestrian on its left and potential oncoming vehicles when the driver of the vehicle behind the Zoox vehicle made contact with the rear bumper of the Zoox vehicle.  There were no injuries.

A Zoox vehicle was proceeding straight in autonomy through an intersection with a green light and right of way when vehicle 2 attempted an illegal left turn across lanes of traffic into Zoox’s right of way. The safety driver disengaged and applied max braking effort which allowed Zoox to mitigate but not completely prevent the unavoidable collision. The Zoox vehicle struck the right front corner of vehicle 2. No injuries were reported and the police were not called to the scene.

A Zoox vehicle in autonomy was stopped at a red light waiting for traffic ahead on Embarcadero with brake lights illuminated. When the traffic light changed to green, surrounding traffic began to move. The Zoox vehicle appropriately continued to wait for a stopped lead vehicle immediately ahead when vehicle 2 struck the Zoox vehicle from the rear. Zoox vehicle camera footage shows the driver of vehicle 2 holding their cellphone raised in their hand at the time of contact. There were no injuries and police were not called.

A Zoox vehicle in autonomous mode was proceeding straight in its lane on Mason Street in San Francisco, CA when an occupant of a parallel parked car (Vehicle 2) abruptly opened its rear passenger side door into the side of the Zoox vehicle, causing minor damage to both vehicles. The Zoox operator disengaged as a result of the contact. There were no injuries and the police were not called.

A stopped Zoox vehicle in autonomous mode was struck by a passenger vehicle that approached it at low speed from behind. The Zoox vehicle incurred damage to its sensors and rear bumper. There were no injuries and the police were not called.

A Zoox vehicle in autonomous mode was stopped at a traffic light on Brannan Street at 7th Street when a passenger vehicle hit the Zoox vehicle from behind. The passenger vehicle left the scene without exchanging information. There were no injuries and the police were not called.
A Zoox vehicle in autonomous mode was stopped in traffic when a passenger vehicle from behind made contact with the rear of the Zoox vehicle at low speed. The police were not called.

A Zoox vehicle in autonomous mode was making a right turn from Bryant Street onto 9th Street when a vehicle overtaking from the rear switched lanes as it drove in front of the Zoox vehicle and made contact with the front Zoox sensors. The other party left the scene. The police were not called and there were no injuries.

location: Kearny St. and Columbus Ave. Intersection
Description: A Zoox vehicle in autonomous mode began to slow down during an unprotected left turn to yield for cross traffic entering the lane from the right. A passenger vehicle from behind did not slow and made contact with the rear sensors of the Zoox vehicle. There were no injuries and the police were not called.

A Zoox vehicle in autonomous mode was stopped on Folsom Street facing Essex Street, when a passenger vehicle from behind made contact with its rear sensors at low speed. The police were not called and there were no injuries.

A Zoox vehicle in autonomous mode was stopped at a red traffic signal at the intersection of Harrison and 11th Streets in San Francisco with its left turn signal engaged. After the traffic signal changed to green and while waiting for an opening to turn left onto Harrison Street, the Zoox vehicle was struck by a passenger vehicle from behind. The driver of that passenger vehicle stated that he was using his phone and not paying attention. No police or emergency services were called to the scene. The Zoox driver, front passenger, and rear passenger reported minor injuries for which they later sought medical attention. The Zoox vehicle incurred minor damage to its rear sensors.

Zoox received an allegation regarding contact between a bicyclist and a Zoox vehicle at the intersection of Harrison and 13th Street in San Francisco. After a thorough search of available sensor data and other internal sources, Zoox was not able to identify any such incident, nor any additional related information including whether a Zoox vehicle was involved or in autonomy.

A Zoox vehicle in autonomy had made a right turn from Oakdell Rd. onto Santa Cruz Ave. in Menlo Park, CA and was preparing to make an immediate, unprotected left turn onto Sharon Road. The Zoox vehicle was slowing and moving at approximately 2 mph with its brake lamps and left turn indicator illuminated, yielding to an oncoming vehicle with the right of way. A following vehicle - traveling at approximately 24 mph - then struck the Zoox vehicle's right rear bumper, and that vehicle's driver airbag appeared to have deployed on impact. The Zoox operator disengaged autonomy, proceeded with the left turn, and pulled over. The following vehicle continued its path of travel, veered out of the lane, and collided with a tree on the left side of the road. The Menlo Park Police Department was called to the scene. Two Zoox operators sustained minor injuries and it is unknown if the driver of the other vehicle sustained injuries.

location: On Kearny St. towards Bush St.
Description: A Zoox vehicle in autonomy was proceeding straight on Kearney Street in San Francisco, CA, in stop-and-go traffic. The Zoox vehicle came to a stop for a vehicle ahead when Vehicle Two made light contact with the Zoox vehicle's rear bumper from behind. There were no injuries and the police were not called.

A Zoox vehicle in autonomy was slowing for a right turn from Treat Ave. to Alameda St. in San Francisco, CA with its turn indicator and brake lights illuminated, when a following bicyclist struck the rear right corner of the Zoox vehicle. The Zoox vehicle camera bracket was damaged. Police were not called and no injuries were reported.

location: Folsom St. and Essex St. Intersection
Description: A Zoox vehicle in autonomous mode making a right turn onto Essex St, fro Folsom St., when a passenger vehicle in the left adjacent turn lane encroached into its lane and made contact with the left bumper and sensors of the Zoox vehicle. There were no injuries and the police were not called.

A Zoox vehicle was in autonomy proceeding straight on Pine Street in San Francisco, CA when it encountered a double parked United States Postal Service van in lane (vehicle 2: model, year, VIN and insurance are unknown). The Zoox vehicle came to a complete stop while waiting for an opportunity to merge around vehicle 2. Vehicle 2 then rolled backwards into the Zoox vehicle, causing minor damage to front sensors and Vehicle 2 rear bumper. There were no injuries and first responders were not notified. Post incident review did not observe any brake lights or reverse lights on vehicle 2 while it was rolling backwards.

A Zoox vehicle in autonomy was proceeding straight on Folsom Street when a leading vehicle in the lane began to slow down prompting the Zoox vehicle to slow correspondingly. The Zoox vehicle, with brake lights illuminated, had slowed to 5 mph when it was struck from the rear by vehicle number 2. Zoox vehicle camera footage shows the driver of vehicle 2 holding their cellphone raised in their right hand. There were no injuries and police were not called.

A Zoox vehicle in autonomy was fully stopped with brake lights illuminated in the left turn lane at a red traffic light waiting to complete a left hand turn from Harrison St. onto 11th St in San Francisco, Ca. As the light turned green, the Zoox vehicle appropriately yielded to oncoming traffic when Vehicle 2 attempted to make a lane change to the right and struck the rear of the Zoox vehicle. The Zoox vehicle incurred minor damage to the rear sensors and bumper. There were no injuries and police were not called.

A Zoox vehicle (Vehicle 1) in autonomy was stopped at a red traffic light on northbound Capp St at the intersection with 24th St in San Francisco. At that time, an SUV (Vehicle 2), heading southbound on Capp St, failed to stop for the red traffic light and entered the intersection, causing a collision with a passenger car (Vehicle 3) that was traveling eastbound on 24th Street. The SUV spun after making contact with the passenger car and collided with the stopped Zoox vehicle, damaging the front bumper on the driver’s side and driver’s side fender, mirror, and sensors on the Zoox vehicle. The police and EMS personnel were called to the scene. The driver of the SUV left the scene without exchanging information. The passenger car appeared to sustain significant damage to the front end. There were no reported injuries. ؆؆؆

A Zoox vehicle (Vehicle 1) in autonomy was stopped at a red traffic light on northbound Capp St at the intersection with 24th St in San Francisco. At that time, an SUV (Vehicle 2), heading southbound on Capp St, failed to stop for the red traffic light and entered the intersection, causing a collision with a passenger car (Vehicle 3) that was traveling eastbound on 24th Street. The SUV spun after making contact with the passenger car and collided with the stopped Zoox vehicle, damaging the front bumper on the driver’s side and driver’s side fender, mirror, and sensors on the Zoox vehicle. The police and EMS personnel were called to the scene. The driver of the SUV left the scene without exchanging information. The passenger car appeared to sustain significant damage to the front end. There were no reported injuries. ؆؆؆

location: On Stockton St near Union St
Description: A Zoox vehicle (Vehicle 1) in autonomy was traveling on southbound Stockton St near Union St in San Francisco. The Zoox vehicle slowed to a gradual stop with brake and hazard lights activated during a simulated pick up-drop off maneuver when it was rear-ended by a minivan (Vehicle 2). The rear bumper of the Zoox vehicle sustained minor damage. There were no reported injuries, and police were not called. Zoox vehicle camera footage shows that the driver of the minivan may not have been looking ahead at the roadway prior to and at the time of contact.

A Zoox vehicle (Vehicle 1) in autonomy, traveling northeast on Mission St, was stopped in lane for a red traffic light at 9th Street. A SamTrans bus (Vehicle 2), with a front-mounted triple-bike rack extending past the width of the bus on the driver's side, was traveling southeast on 9th Street and attempting a right turn onto Mission St. The protruding edge of the bike rack was encroaching into the Zoox vehicle's travel lane as the bus was executing the right hand turn. As the light turned green the Zoox vehicle inched forward and attempted to steer away from the bus. Just as the safety operator disengaged from autonomy, the protruding edge of the bike rack made contact with the driver's side fender on the Zoox vehicle. There were no reported injuries and the police were not called.

location: Kearny Street and Commercial Street Intersection
Description: A Zoox vehicle in autonomy was proceeding northbound on Kearny Street in stop-and-go traffic through an active construction zone. At the same time, an e-scooter traveling near the right curb was passing other slow traffic behind the Zoox vehicle. Before the e-scooter could also pass the Zoox vehicle on the right, the e-scooter weaved away from the curb, seemingly to avoid a drainage grate, and came within a close following distance behind the Zoox vehicle. As the Zoox vehicle came to a stop again for traffic ahead the e-scooter rider did not stop, and the e-scooter made contact with the right rear tail light of the Zoox vehicle. The e-scooter rider remained upright, did not stop to exchange information, and immediately rode off while the Zoox vehicle was still stopped. There were no injuries and police were not called. The damage to the Zoox vehicle was limited to a cracked tail light lens.

A Zoox vehicle in autonomous mode was traveling north on Harrison St. The Zoox vehicle began coming to a gradual stop for traffic ahead when it was rear ended by vehicle 2 at low speed. There was minor damage and police were not called. The Zoox operator reported a "sore neck and back."

location: Pacific Ave., Kearny St., Columbus Ave. Intersectio
Description: A Zoox vehicle in autonomous mode was proceeding westbound with the right of way on a green traffic light at the six way intersection of Pacific Ave., Keary St., and Columbus Ave., when a person operating an electric scooter ran a red light and proceeded northbound into the intersection. The scooter made contact with the left rear quarter panel of the Zoox vehicle, at which time the Zoox vehicle had disengaged from autonomous mode. The Zoox vehicle pulled over, and police and emergency services arrived at the scene. Zoox is submitting this updated report to correct a previous reporting error in the injury field and to update for additional information received in August 2022. This update provides complete information for this incident.

A Zoox vehicle in autonomy was slowing to a gradual stop on eastbound Folsom St. for a red light at 7th St. when it was rear-ended by vehicle 2 at approximately 10 mph. There was minor damage, no reported injuries, and police were not called.
